				<td colspan="2"><span>LOL, let me just preface this by saying that I completely understand why...but I still just miss my weaps.  I'm almost 40 and have been using a pair of Steel Laced Aged Snake Whips (12/18 +4Agi, +5 SvMagic).  
<br />

<br />
The newest patch didn't mention it in the patch message, but they ever so sneakily added a required level of 60 to these weapons, meaning when I went to try and equip them to try out /melody and do a little fear kiting, I was instead off to the bazaar to see what I could find.
<br />

<br />
I guess I should say that, on one hand, i'm happy...since this means that I will have a reason to equip my barbarian warrior with something besides 2 whips that just don't fit his style <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Anyhoo..just had to gripe a bit before letting it go, was anyone else caught by surprise by this?  I just bought these during Thanksgiving break when I made my bard.
<br />

<br />
Also, I just bought a guardian mace (14/24) and a vengeful honed blade of the ykesha (12/21, 10/21 for now) to replace the glorious whips that I had for my bard.  Does this sound like an okay setup for someone that doesn't have much money to spend?
<br />

<br />
And one final question, my wife has a pair of these on her warrior...will she be able to keep them equipped until she dies for the first time?  Unfortunately, they weren't equipped on my warrior since I switched them back and forth between him and my bard.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for any help and thanks for just givin me a place to do a bit of griping before moving on.</span></td>
