				<td colspan="2"><span>Pff, I had it worse off.  So shortly after they brought out Caverns of Exile zone (Sol C) I managed to get my hands on a Shadowflame (2hs 41dmg/44del and other really nifty stats) because noone else in group could use it at the time and it was actually Bard usable.  
<br />

<br />
So I'd put this on and hit dark elf illusion and run around as a Shadow Knight and the best was having friends ask what it was, I'd link and they'd get pissed because a bard was using a better 2hs than they had.  I hit for like a max of 72, and was having a blast owning decaying skeles by the newbies and just generally confusing everyone.  Since when can SK mez?!? <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-7.gif" border="0" alt="Perplexed" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I also had it in my collection of bard usable 2h weps such as Overthere Hammer for 2hb and Goranga Spear for 2hpierce.  I'm still looking for a bard usable bow, I swear I saw 1 in the baz once when looking for ranged items there was this nice bard usable bow, but was cost WAY more than I had, and I have not seen it since. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" />  
<br />

<br />
Well as I'm sure you can imagine, I was quite upset when suddenly I was not able to wield it because my class/diety didn't allow it.  I'm thinking wtf?!?  I pay closer look and notice they removed BRD from usable classes.  
<br />

<br />
I REALLY wished they would have at least done the old school nerf where the orignals didn't change and only the new ones did.  Many friends were as upset as I when I had to destroy such a nice 2hs.  Waste of a really nice toy.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" /></span></td>
